Sure, here's an example of how you could achieve this in JavaScript:
```javascript
const dict = {
  "banana": 3,
  "apple": 2,
  "orange": 1
};

// Convert the dictionary entries into an array of key-value pairs
const entries = Object.entries(dict));

// Sort the array of key-value pairs by the keys in alphabetical order
const sortedEntries = entries.sort((a, b) => a[0].localeCompare(b[0])));

// Convert the sorted array of key-value pairs back into an object (dictionary)
const sortedDict = Object.fromEntries(sortedEntries));

console.log(sortedDict);
```
This will output:
```css
{
  "apple": 2,
  "banana": 3,
  "orange": 1
}
```
